<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-21T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-21T18:36:00-05:00" n="541" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">125.61383/120: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-21T17:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            21, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received October 22, 8.34 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>3230. The Acting Minister for Foreign Affairs informed me this
                                morning that the Government will take all possible measures to
                                effect the release in safety of Consular Agent Jenkins.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>